<h3>
When to use layouts
</h3>

<p>
Use layouts when elements aren't intended to wrap inside the container.
</p>

<p>Layouts use margin to define the gutters between items. The first item doesn't have a left margin and the last item doesn't have a right margin. Every other item divides the gutter in two and puts half of it on the right and half on the left.</p>

<div class='hbox demo'>
<aside>
  <div class='demo-no-wrapping'>
    <div class='box' data-show-margin-left data-show-margin-right></div>
    <div class='box' data-show-margin-left data-show-margin-right></div>
    <div class='box' data-show-margin-left data-show-margin-right></div>
    <div class='box' data-show-margin-left data-show-margin-right></div>
  </div>
</aside>
<aside>
  <div class='demo-bad-wrapping'>
    <div class='box' data-show-margin-left data-show-margin-right></div>
    <div class='box' data-show-margin-left data-show-margin-right></div>
    <div class='box' data-show-margin-left data-show-margin-right></div>
    <div class='box' data-show-margin-left data-show-margin-right></div>
  </div>
</aside>
